Package: sapfluxr
Title: Comprehensive Sap Flow Analysis from Heat Pulse Velocity Sensors
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Grant", "Joyce", email = "neez1977@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = "Developer"),
    person("Gavan", "McGrath", role = "aut",
           comment = "Original R script development"),
    person("Tim", "Bleby", role = "aut",
           comment = "Scientific review and Excel workflow design")
    )
Description: A comprehensive R package for processing and analyzing sap flow data
    from heat pulse velocity sensors. Provides complete pipeline from raw
    temperature measurements to tree-level sap flux calculations, including
    multiple HPV calculation methods (HRM, MHR, HRMXa, HRMXb, Tmax variants),
    data quality control, corrections for probe spacing and wounding effects,
    sapwood area integration, and temporal aggregation. Includes both
    programmatic API and interactive Shiny interface for analysis workflows.
